The first value, 1, indicates the number of images in the array. In this case, there is only one image in the array.

The first value, indicates the height of the image in pixels. The second value, represents the width of the image in pixels. The third value, signifies the number of channels in the image. In this case, it's 3, indicating that the image is in RGB (Red, Green, Blue) color format. So, the image has a resolution of 1080 pixels in height, 810 pixels in width, and consists of three color channels.

In [13]:
def frame_processing(input):
    outcome = pretrained_model(input)
    cv2.imshow('Detection Model', np.squeeze(outcome.render()))

seize = cv2.VideoCapture('Car Crash Compilation _ Dashcam Videos _ Driving Fails  - 266 [USA & Canada Only].mp4')
while True:
    value_returned, input = seize.read()
    
    if not value_returned:
        break
    
    frame_processing(input)
    
    if cv2.waitKey(15) == ord('b'):
        break

seize.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

Image Capturing

In [28]:
pathoffigures = 'essentials/images'
tags = ['concentrated', 'distracted']
numoffigs = 40
In [ ]:
seize = cv2.VideoCapture(0)
for tag in tags:
    print(f"Acquiring images for the {tag}")
    time.sleep(5)
    for fignum in range(numoffigs):
        print(f"Acquiring images for the {tag}, number of image {fignum}")
        value_returned, input = seize.read()
        #here we are using uuid to name the images as if we use fignum new images 
        #are overwriting the older ones
        nameoffig = pathoffigures + '/' + tag + '.' + str(uuid.uuid1()) + '.jpg'
        cv2.imwrite(nameoffig, input)
        cv2.imshow('Image Collection', input)
        time.sleep(5)
        if cv2.waitKey(5) == ord('b'):
            break
seize.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()

In [11]:
def frame_processing(input):
    outcome = custom_model(input)
    cv2.imshow('Detection Model', np.squeeze(outcome.render()))

seize = cv2.VideoCapture(0)
while True:
    value_returned, input = seize.read()
    
    if not value_returned:
        break
    
    frame_processing(input)
    
    if cv2.waitKey(15) == ord('b'):
        break

seize.release()
cv2.destroyAllWindows()
